<i>by Trespassers William)</i>

487
00:43:44,488 --> 00:43:48,185
<i># Oh. The weight it must be light</i>

488
00:43:48,258 --> 00:43:51,694
<i># Wherever you are</i>

489
00:43:54,131 --> 00:43:57,862
# <i>A nd I kndo w ydou doon't tthlnk ttwlicdo</i>

490
00:43:57,935 --> 00:44:01,132
<i># Wherever you are</i>

491
00:44:03,674 --> 00:44:07,405
# <i>A nd doo ydou tthlnk dofmdo, ydou mlghtt,</i>

492
00:44:07,478 --> 00:44:10,811
<i># Wherever you are</i>

493
00:44:16,787 --> 00:44:20,723
- What are you doing here?
- You know, just scoping out johns.

494
00:44:22,660 --> 00:44:25,151
You want a beer?

495
00:44:25,229 --> 00:44:27,129
Nah.

496
00:44:27,197 --> 00:44:29,358
How's your leave been?

497
00:44:29,967 --> 00:44:33,266
It's been a blast. How's yours?

498
00:44:33,337 --> 00:44:36,397
- OK.
<i>- (slow music on the jukebox)</i>

499
00:44:36,473 --> 00:44:39,738
You looking forward to heading back?

500
00:44:40,177 --> 00:44:43,408
Come on.
I thought you were gonna dance with me.

501
00:44:58,562 --> 00:45:01,497
I'm sorry. Do you mind if I cut in?

502
00:45:13,677 --> 00:45:16,510
This is nice.

503
00:45:16,580 --> 00:45:19,879
I don't think I've danced since high school.

504
00:45:20,584 --> 00:45:23,951
- No spring dances at the academy?
- No.

505
00:45:24,021 --> 00:45:26,353
Uh-uh. Never gone.

506
00:45:27,458 --> 00:45:29,221
Yeah, you can tell.

507
00:45:29,293 --> 00:45:31,761
Really? Says the guy
who keep stepping on my foot.

508
00:45:31,829 --> 00:45:33,820
Ow!

509
00:45:33,897 --> 00:45:36,365
Sorry.

510
00:45:39,303 --> 00:45:41,601
Why don't you go to the dances?

511
00:45:43,540 --> 00:45:48,239
Some guys at the academy
don't view women as their equals.

512
00:45:48,312 --> 00:45:51,213
It's worse if you start dating them.

513
00:45:54,151 --> 00:45:56,813
It's no fun being underestimated, is it?

514
00:46:00,257 --> 00:46:03,715
It's worse when you do it to yourself.

515
00:46:12,269 --> 00:46:14,260
Excuse me.

516
00:46:16,306 --> 00:46:19,537
I will see you tomorrow, Plebe Huard.

517
00:46:20,944 --> 00:46:23,276
Watch your feet.

518
00:46:41,465 --> 00:46:43,194
- Delta Company.
- Sir.

519
00:46:43,267 --> 00:46:48,762
One missing and unaccounted for.
Midshipman Fourth Class Butcher.

520
00:46:54,278 --> 00:46:57,736
- Echo Company.
- Sir, two missing and unaccounted for.

521
00:46:57,815 --> 00:47:00,079
Midshipman Fourth Class Casarico,

522
00:47:00,150 --> 00:47:02,141
Midshipman Fourth Class Huard.

523
00:47:07,124 --> 00:47:12,619
Ma'am, Midshipman Fourth Class Huard
is present and accounted for, ma'am.

524
00:47:22,472 --> 00:47:26,806
- In case you forgot, we wear uniform here.
- Sir, yes, sir.

525
00:47:26,877 --> 00:47:30,438
- Put yourself on report.
- Sir, aye aye, sir.

526
00:47:38,956 --> 00:47:43,086
- Memorial Hall in ten, Huard.
- Sir, aye aye, sir.

527
00:48:00,410 --> 00:48:02,435
Dead at 23.

528
00:48:03,580 --> 00:48:06,549
The best officer I ever served under.

529
00:48:08,218 --> 00:48:10,584
I'm sorry about your friend, sir.

530
00:48:10,654 --> 00:48:13,623
Why? He's not.

531
00:48:17,327 --> 00:48:19,921
Why are you here, Huard?

532
00:48:20,697 --> 00:48:22,790
To serve my country, sir.

533
00:48:23,400 --> 00:48:25,732
You say that here...

534
00:48:26,770 --> 00:48:30,729
where people actually died
for their country.

535
00:48:31,675 --> 00:48:34,269
You don't think I took Psych 101?

536
00:48:35,412 --> 00:48:38,245
You're here to answer the question
that's gnawed at you

537
00:48:38,315 --> 00:48:42,945
ever since you saw this place
from across the river.

538
00:48:43,020 --> 00:48:45,818
Well, let me spare you the suspense.

539
00:48:46,757 --> 00:48:48,691
You ain't good enough.

540
00:48:48,759 --> 00:48:51,159
I've heard that my whole life.

541
00:48:52,930 --> 00:48:54,659
But I'm still here.

542
00:48:56,266 --> 00:49:01,499
All the other company commanders here,
they're playing soldier.

543
00:49:02,506 --> 00:49:04,633
But I've been a soldier, Huard.

544
00:49:05,909 --> 00:49:08,969
I've seen what good officers are like.

545
00:49:11,014 --> 00:49:13,983
And I know what bad officers are like.

546
00:49:15,485 --> 00:49:20,445
So there ain't no way
I'm letting someone finish this year

547
00:49:20,524 --> 00:49:23,721
who's not worthy of this academy.

548
00:49:23,794 --> 00:49:26,661
I'm not quitting.

549
00:49:30,367 --> 00:49:35,168
<i>(Whitaker)</i> Wakey wakey!
Come on, Loo. Move, butterball!

550
00:49:35,973 --> 00:49:38,942
<i>(Cole)</i> Plebe Huard.
How many missiles are the Ohio class

551
00:49:39,009 --> 00:49:42,911
of ballistic missile submarines
capable of carrying?

552
00:49:42,980 --> 00:49:44,538
Sir, I'll find out, sir.

553
00:49:46,450 --> 00:49:52,355
Who was the youngest midshipman,
and how old was he?

554
00:49:53,090 --> 00:49:55,923
Sir, I'll find out, sir.

555
00:49:55,993 --> 00:49:58,325
I'm sure you will, Huard.

556
00:49:58,395 --> 00:50:00,863
Keep filling.

557
00:50:09,239 --> 00:50:10,467
<i>(whispers)</i> Stop.

558
00:50:13,677 --> 00:50:16,145
Congratulations, Loo.

559
00:50:17,714 --> 00:50:22,310
You can join Huard
on marching tours this weekend.

560
00:50:23,086 --> 00:50:24,644
Carry on.

561
00:50:24,721 --> 00:50:27,019
Understand this.

562
00:50:27,090 --> 00:50:32,255
When Plebe Huard
doesn't know his rates, none of you do.

563
00:50:33,263 --> 00:50:36,824
A company is only as strong
as its weakest plebe.

564
00:50:49,579 --> 00:50:53,709
You should get out too, Nance.
He's just gonna drag you down.

565
00:50:54,718 --> 00:50:57,050
He's right, you know.

566
00:50:59,289 --> 00:51:01,621
Can I borrow your starch?

567
00:51:02,659 --> 00:51:05,753
Look, I don't get it.
Why are you still here?

568
00:51:06,663 --> 00:51:10,963
- You want to know why I stay in this room?
- Yeah.

569
00:51:11,034 --> 00:51:14,197
'Cause, Jake, you're my Mississippi.

570
00:51:14,905 --> 00:51:17,032
I'm your what?

571
00:51:17,107 --> 00:51:21,009
People who live in Arkansas,
you know what their favorite state is?

572
00:51:21,078 --> 00:51:22,204
No.

573
00:51:22,279 --> 00:51:26,579
Mississippi. 'Cause Mississippi's
the only thing that keeps Arkansas

574
00:51:26,650 --> 00:51:30,177
from being the worst state
in the whole country.

575
00:51:30,253 --> 00:51:35,088
- I'm Mississippi.
- Well, you sure as hell ain't California.

576
00:51:35,158 --> 00:51:38,093
Listen, Cole and Whitaker
are so busy trying to run you out

577
00:51:38,161 --> 00:51:40,629
they forgot all about me.

578
00:51:40,697 --> 00:51:47,728
As a matter of fact, they've forgotten about
every other plebe in this whole company.

579
00:51:47,804 --> 00:51:52,571
That's why I stay in this room, Jake.
'Cause if Mississippi quits,

580
00:51:52,642 --> 00:51:57,739
then all of a sudden Arkansas
is the worst state in the whole country.

581
00:51:59,116 --> 00:52:01,448
Hey, where's my starch?

582
00:52:01,518 --> 00:52:04,146
- All right.
- Come on, chop chop.

583
00:52:13,830 --> 00:52:16,526
You're looking good, Huard.

584
00:52:16,600 --> 00:52:20,229
Pretty soon you'll be able
to keep up with my six-year-old daughter.

585
00:52:20,303 --> 00:52:23,033
When can I start boxing again, sir?

586
00:52:23,106 --> 00:52:25,904
When I make admiral.

587
00:52:25,976 --> 00:52:31,073
You knew better than to pull
that mess you pulled in my ring, son.

588
00:52:39,022 --> 00:52:41,115
Eyes on the ring.

589
00:52:41,191 --> 00:52:44,217
Brigades Tournament
begins in eight weeks.

590
00:52:44,294 --> 00:52:46,854
Training starts this Friday.

591
00:52:46,930 --> 00:52:52,334
Brigades is the biggest event
in this academy all year. You know why?

592
00:52:52,402 --> 00:52:58,068
Because the boxing ring is the only place
in this academy where everybody's equal.

593
00:52:58,141 --> 00:53:01,804
Doesn't matter what your rank is,
how many stripes you got,

594
00:53:01,878 --> 00:53:07,180
the only thing that is guaranteed
when you step inside these ropes:

595
00:53:08,852 --> 00:53:11,548
You're gonna find out who you are.

596
00:53:23,867 --> 00:53:26,631
This doesn't look like your room.

597
00:53:28,171 --> 00:53:31,265
What are you doing here, Huard?

598
00:53:31,341 --> 00:53:33,502
I'm training for the Brigades, sir.

599
00:53:35,845 --> 00:53:38,279
All right, Huard.

600
00:53:38,348 --> 00:53:40,339
Let's see how you're doing.

601
00:53:41,117 --> 00:53:43,347
Sir?

602
00:53:43,420 --> 00:53:45,911
Show me how
you're gonna win the Brigades.

603
00:53:47,991 --> 00:53:50,323
<i>(Burton)</i> Ding ding.

604
00:53:51,528 --> 00:53:55,259
Don't worry, Huard.
I'm not your company officer in here.

605
00:53:55,332 --> 00:53:58,460
I'm just a guy
looking to punch you in the mouth.

606
00:53:58,535 --> 00:54:03,802
Well, you can take a punch.
I guess we knew that already, didn't we?

607
00:54:06,243 --> 00:54:08,973
You can actually land a punch, too.

608
00:54:14,217 --> 00:54:16,344
- You're pretty good, Huard.
- Thanks.

609
00:54:16,419 --> 00:54:19,411
Against a 36-year-old
out-of-shape lieutenant.

610
00:54:32,035 --> 00:54:34,526
Not bad, Huard.

611
00:54:34,604 --> 00:54:39,405
You know, most of the boxers in the
Brigades are nationally ranked amateurs.

612
00:54:39,476 --> 00:54:42,809
Think you're gonna beat 'em
by hitting the bag for a couple hours?

613
00:54:42,879 --> 00:54:44,870
I'll do what I have to.

614
00:54:44,948 --> 00:54:48,111
Really? Without anyone training you?

615
00:54:48,184 --> 00:54:52,883
You think you're gonna be the first plebe
to get through here without anyone's help?

616
00:54:52,956 --> 00:54:55,356
I don't need anyone's help.

617
00:55:06,002 --> 00:55:08,698
No one thinks I'll make it anyway.

618
00:55:15,512 --> 00:55:20,245
Who do you think convinced the board
to take a chance on you?

619
00:55:24,954 --> 00:55:31,518
This ain't the shipyard, Huard. You can't
just will yourself through this place.

620
00:55:55,085 --> 00:55:56,882
Sorry. I'll be done in a minute.

621
00:56:04,928 --> 00:56:11,265
Here. Recent studies show that auditory
retention surpasses that of visual retention.

622
00:56:13,336 --> 00:56:14,360
OK.

623
00:56:14,437 --> 00:56:17,998
OK. Turn off the light
so I can get some sleep.

624
00:56:23,446 --> 00:56:25,937
<i>(Nance's voice)</i>
<i>What is the latitude of Annapolis?</i>

625
00:56:26,015 --> 00:56:29,246
<i>The latitude of Annapolis is 38.58° north.</i>

626
00:56:29,319 --> 00:56:30,411
Thanks.

627
00:56:37,293 --> 00:56:39,625
- Ma'am.
- Plebe Huard.

628
00:56:41,831 --> 00:56:44,322
- Everything OK?
- Yes, ma'am.

629
00:56:45,735 --> 00:56:48,067
You know I'm training for the Brigades.

630
00:56:48,138 --> 00:56:51,403
That's great, Huard. Good luck.

631
00:56:51,474 --> 00:56:53,704
Maybe we could work out together.

632
00:56:53,777 --> 00:56:56,940
Uh, no. I think I'm already
in pretty good shape, thanks.

633
00:56:57,013 --> 00:56:59,345
Ma'am.

634
00:57:02,485 --> 00:57:05,181
I need your help.

635
00:57:28,878 --> 00:57:32,177
What? Think you're gonna be
all alone in that ring?

636
00:57:36,085 --> 00:57:38,246
Come on. Come on.

637
00:57:38,321 --> 00:57:40,755
- Let's go.
- Come on.

638
00:57:56,973 --> 00:57:59,373
- Damn it.
- Come on.

639
00:58:00,109 --> 00:58:03,306
Before you achieve, you must believe.

640
00:58:03,379 --> 00:58:05,438
Let's go, Arkansas.

641
00:58:18,661 --> 00:58:23,155
Come on, Huard.
I've seen better footwork at Payless.

642
00:58:23,233 --> 00:58:24,700
Come on, get back in there.

643
00:58:24,767 --> 00:58:28,066
Better footwork at Payless?

644
00:58:48,725 --> 00:58:51,523
- Jake.
- What?

645
00:58:53,429 --> 00:58:57,763
You're trying to get into
Cole's weight class, right?

646
00:58:59,802 --> 00:59:01,667
Yeah.

647
00:59:05,341 --> 00:59:06,672
What's this?

648
00:59:06,743 --> 00:59:10,839
Well, you're not gonna get there
by just eating the stuff they serve you here.

649
00:59:10,914 --> 00:59:15,874
What you need, my friend, is the patented
Marcus Nance North Beach Diet,

650
00:59:15,952 --> 00:59:18,819
which, I'm proud to say,

651
00:59:18,888 --> 00:59:25,384
has been perfected
after 18 years of dedicated research.

652
00:59:26,696 --> 00:59:29,790
- So you're gonna get me to 185?
- Hey.

653
00:59:29,866 --> 00:59:33,768
I'm not only the president
of the Marcus Nance North Beach Diet,

654
00:59:33,836 --> 00:59:36,236
I'm also a client.

655
01:00:04,300 --> 01:00:06,825
Come on, get down in the mud.
Come on. Come on, buddy.

656
01:00:06,903 --> 01:00:09,804
Up, up. Over, over.
Go, Arkansas. Come on.

657
01:00:09,872 --> 01:00:10,964
Let me see you run.

658
01:00:14,978 --> 01:00:17,776
<i>(Nance) How long have you been</i>
<i>in the Navy? All my bloomin' life.</i>

659
01:00:21,718 --> 01:00:25,586
Just hook it over and we're done.
Hook it over and we're done. Here we go.

660
01:00:38,267 --> 01:00:40,292
What happened to all my ball machines?

661
01:00:43,072 --> 01:00:46,599
- Come on, Huard. Dance for me.
- Hit me once and you can talk like that.

662
01:00:46,676 --> 01:00:50,168
- I have. I think I hit you about five times.
- Ooh!

663
01:00:50,246 --> 01:00:52,578
Make that six, Huard.

664
01:01:01,391 --> 01:01:04,292
Three. That's three. Gimme one more.

665
01:01:04,360 --> 01:01:07,329
That was for momma.
Gimme one for daddy. Get up there.

666
01:01:07,397 --> 01:01:10,059
How bad do you want it?
How bad do you want it?

667
01:01:23,179 --> 01:01:25,511
Not quite there, huh?

668
01:01:28,184 --> 01:01:30,209
Come on. How bad do you want it?

669
01:02:05,922 --> 01:02:08,254
OK, that's good. Stop.

670
01:02:23,906 --> 01:02:26,033
I never could have done it.

671
01:02:28,244 --> 01:02:30,269
What?

672
01:02:30,346 --> 01:02:34,976
Made it through plebe year
if I could see my home every day.

673
01:02:36,619 --> 01:02:42,649
Well, if I couldn't see it every day,
I probably would have quit a long time ago.

674
01:02:47,697 --> 01:02:51,428
You know, my mom
used to take me out here.

675
01:02:51,501 --> 01:02:53,526
We had a Sunfish.

676
01:02:53,603 --> 01:02:55,935
We'd park it down there.

677
01:03:00,743 --> 01:03:05,373
She was the only person
who ever believed I'd make it here.

678
01:03:05,448 --> 01:03:08,144
She must be very proud of you.

679
01:03:09,485 --> 01:03:11,817
She would be.

680
01:03:13,623 --> 01:03:15,989
I'm sorry.

681
01:03:18,528 --> 01:03:21,326
She's what's getting you through?

682
01:03:23,466 --> 01:03:27,197
Well... She's what got me here.

683
01:03:29,272 --> 01:03:33,038
But she's not the one
who's getting me through.

684
01:03:46,689 --> 01:03:48,748
Matt Cole, 197.

685
01:03:48,825 --> 01:03:51,726
All right, Midshipman. You step down.

686
01:03:53,196 --> 01:03:55,289
Anybody else for heavyweight?

687
01:03:57,600 --> 01:04:03,095
- All right, I guess that's it, then.
<i>- (Nance)</i> One more heavyweight.

688
01:04:09,478 --> 01:04:12,038
- Huard, what are you doing?
- Weighing in.

689
01:04:12,114 --> 01:04:15,515
Jump rope contest is next week.
My daughter's looking forward to it.

690
01:04:15,585 --> 01:04:17,678
- Anybody else?
- Sir.

691
01:04:17,753 --> 01:04:21,018
You said the Brigades
were open to all midshipmen.

692
01:04:21,090 --> 01:04:23,183
I want to fight.

693
01:04:30,199 --> 01:04:35,535
Fine. I'm gonna draw up a permission slip
for your parents to sign. Hit the scales.

694
01:04:55,424 --> 01:04:57,756
Jake Huard, 185.

695
01:06:14,537 --> 01:06:16,300
Next up, heavyweight division:

696
01:06:16,372 --> 01:06:19,136
Midshipman Loo
versus Midshipman Huard.

697
01:06:19,208 --> 01:06:22,302
- Let's go.
<i>- (crowd chants)</i> Loo! Loo! Loo! Loo!

698
01:06:22,378 --> 01:06:24,710
<i>(chanting continues)</i>

699
01:06:29,385 --> 01:06:32,582
You both received your instructions
in the dressing rooms.

700
01:06:32,655 --> 01:06:35,089
I want you to keep it clean.
Any questions?

701
01:06:35,157 --> 01:06:37,489
Payback's a bitch, Huard.

702
01:06:42,198 --> 01:06:45,258
You set the pace out there, Huard.

703
01:06:45,334 --> 01:06:46,858
<i>(bell)</i>

704
01:07:09,191 --> 01:07:11,284
Come on, Jake. One more.

705
01:07:11,360 --> 01:07:13,260
Hmm? Come on, hit me one time.

706
01:07:16,899 --> 01:07:19,891
One, two, three,

707
01:07:19,969 --> 01:07:23,905
four, five, six, seven,

708
01:07:23,973 --> 01:07:26,441
eight, nine, ten.

709
01:07:26,509 --> 01:07:27,840
You're out.

710
01:07:33,082 --> 01:07:34,777
What is the latitude of Annapolis?

711
01:07:34,850 --> 01:07:38,718
